    <h1>Concept Library Test Specification</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"ConceptLibraryTestSpecification-Permissions(allofthebelow=
forconceptsandworkingsets)">Permissions (all of the below for concepts and =
working sets)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Verify that a user with edit rights who is not an owner cannot change t=
he permissions.</li>
<li>Verify that a user can transfer ownership to a different user
<ul>
<li>The new user is displayed as the owner in the concept.</li>
<li>The new user can edit the concept and edit permissions.</li>
<li>The old user can no longer edit permissions</li>
<li>The old user no longer has view/edit if they don't have this via a grou=
p etc.</li>
</ul></li>
<li>Verify that when a new concept is created and no changes are made to th=
e permissions, only the owner can view and edit the concept.</li>
<li>Verify that if everyone is set to "view", a different user can view the=
 concept but not edit it.</li>
<li>Verify that if everyone is set to "edit" a different user can view and =
edit the concept.</li>
<li>Verify that if group is set to "view", a different group member can vie=
w the concept but not edit it.</li>
<li>Verify that if group is set to "edit" a different group member can view=
 and edit the concept.</li>
<li>Verify that if group is set to "edit" and everyone "none", a non-group =
member cannot view or edit.</li>
<li>Verify that a super user can do everything, regardless of permission se=
ttings.</li>
<li>Verify that if permission to a concept is revoked, a concept/working se=
t referring to it cannot export codes via the UI or the API, and there is a=
n error message displayed.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"ConceptLibraryTestSpecification-Readonlyapplicationconfiguration"=
>Read only application configuration</h2>
<ul>
<li>A concept owner cannot edit.</li>
<li>A user cannot create a new concept.</li>
<li>A user cannot revert a concept.</li>
<li>A user cannot fork a concept.</li>
<li>A super user CANNOT create, edit, revert, or fork a concept.</li>
<li>A user cannot edit by creating their own URL string to bypass the inter=
face.</li>
<li>The database user in this application configuration cannot edit any tab=
le that stores concept information.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"ConceptLibraryTestSpecification-Versioning">Versioning</h2>
<ul>
<li>Every version of a code list has a version ID (formerly the history ID)=
</li>
<li>The version ID is displayed along with the title.</li>
<li>There is a URL to refer to a specific version of a code list</li>
<li>There is a URL that always refers to the latest version of a code list<=
/li>
<li>The API can get a specific version of a code list</li>
<li>The API can get the latest version of a code list</li>
<li>When a child concept is added to a parent concept, it adds the latest v=
ersion by default (but the version number can be changed).</li>
<li>When a child concept is updated, the parent concept does not change</li=
>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Repeat all of the above for working sets.</p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"ConceptLibraryTestSpecification-WorkingSets">Working Sets</h2>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"ConceptLibraryTestSpecification-HierarchicalCodeLists">Hierarchic=
al Code Lists</h2>
<p><em>Key requirements: a code list with a particular version never change=
s or becomes inaccessible due to changes in other code lists.</em></p>
<ul>
<li>When a child concept is added to a concept or working set, the latest v=
ersion is always added.</li>
<li>When a child concept is updated, any concept or working set that contai=
ns it automatically generates a new version. The update happens recursively=
.</li>
<li>The version history shows this update as "Concept blah blah changed, au=
tomatic update" or something, and the user field makes it clear that this w=
as a system update, not a user update.</li>
<li>When a user clicks "revert" or "fork" on a historical version of a conc=
ept or working set that has a child, there is a warning message "the new ve=
rsion will refer to the latest version of child concepts. Continue? Yes/no"=
</li>
</ul>
<p><em><br></em></p>
<p><em><br></em></p>
<ul>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>When one code list includes another code list as a component, the paren=
t code list takes a copy of the codes, and it doesn't change when the child=
 changes.</li>
<li>The parent code list stores and displays the version of the child code =
list that was used.</li>
<li>If the child code list is no longer the latest version (and there is ac=
cess), then there is an "update" functionality to click a button and update=
 the child to the latest.</li>
<li>If the user no longer has access to view the child code list, this is h=
ighlighted with a warning.</li>
<li>A concept cannot be added as a child if you don't have permission to us=
e that concept (i.e. view permission on all descendants).</li>
<li>A concept cannot be added as a child if it would create a circular situ=
ation (the current concept would be its own descendant). Test this with 4 l=
evels of inheritance.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"ConceptLibraryTestSpecification-Exclusions">Exclusions</h2>
<ul>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>If a code is included within one component and excluded within another =
component, it will not be included in the output.</li>
<li>If a code is included multiple times within different components, it wi=
ll only be included once in the output.</li>
<li>If a code is included multiple times and excluded, it will be excluded.=
</li>
</ul>
</ul>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"ConceptLibraryTestSpecification-RegularExpressions">Regular Expre=
ssions</h2>
<ul>
<ul>
<ul>
<li>The match with expression functionality makes a copy of the codes, and =
the code list does not change if the lookup table changes.</li>
</ul>
</ul>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
